bark "Narrator: Bimba waits by her food bowl while the house still sleeps."

So, my wife has a labrador
She has 2 toys
Her name is "Bimba"

bark "Narrator: Bimba's cookie jar sits on the counter, tempting her nose..."

her cookie jar holds some items: "cookie", "cookie", "cookie", "cookie"
memory is count of the items in the cookie jar
her toy box holds some items: "ball", "squeaky toy", "stick"

bark: "Narrator: with the jar out of her reach, she decides to focus on her toys."
when she has 4 toys then she woofs "time to play!" otherwise she whines "I want more toys!"

bark "Narrator: with the humans still asleep it is time to play, but first Bimba needs more toys!"
she snags a toy
the toy box loses the first item
she snags a toy
the toy box loses the first item
she snags a toy
the toy box loses the first item
bark "Narrator: Greedy dogs always take more than one toy, three in this case!"

